    Exercise(id: "hammerCurlDumbbell", name: "Hammer Curl (Dumbbell)", description: "Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides with palms facing your body. Keep your elbows close to your torso and curl the dumbbells upward toward your shoulders, focusing on squeezing your biceps. Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position with control. Maintain a neutral wrist throughout the exercise and avoid swinging the weights to ensure you're targeting your biceps effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .dumbbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Hang Clean (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "hangCleanBarbell", name: "Hang Clean (Barbell)", description: "Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart and the barbell on the floor in front of you. Bend at your knees and hips to grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back flat, chest up, and core engaged. Explosively extend your hips, knees, and ankles to lift the barbell off the floor. As the barbell reaches hip level, quickly shrug your shoulders and pull the barbell upward. Drop under the barbell and catch it in a front squat position with elbows high. Stand up to complete the movement. Lower the barbell back down to the starting position in a controlled manner. Focus on generating power from your lower body and maintaining proper form throughout the exercise.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Hang Snatch (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "hangSnatchBarbell", name: "Hang Snatch (Barbell)", description: "Start in a similar position as the hang clean, but with a wider grip on the barbell. Perform the initial pull as in the hang clean, but instead of catching the barbell in a front squat position, continue pulling the barbell overhead in one fluid motion. Drop under the barbell into a partial squat or split stance to catch it overhead with locked elbows. Stand up to complete the lift, then lower the barbell back down under control to the starting position. Focus on explosive power from your hips and legs, as well as precise timing and coordination to execute the snatch effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Hip Abductor (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "hipAbductorMachine", name: "Hip Abductor (Machine)", description: "To perform hip abductor exercises on a machine, sit comfortably with your back against the backrest and adjust the machine's settings to fit your body size. Position your legs against the pads provided, ensuring your knees are aligned with the machine's pivot point. Start by pushing your legs outward against the resistance of the machine, engaging your outer thigh muscles (abductors). Pause briefly when your legs are fully extended, then slowly release back to the starting position. Focus on maintaining controlled movements throughout the exercise to effectively target and strengthen your hip abductors.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Hip Adductor (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "hipAdductorMachine", name: "Hip Adductor (Machine)", description: "Sit on the machine with your back against the backrest and adjust the settings so that the pads fit comfortably against your inner thighs. Start with your legs positioned inside the pads and grasp the handles if provided for stability. Push the pads inward against the resistance of the machine by squeezing your inner thighs (adductors). Hold the contraction briefly when the pads are closest together, then slowly release back to the starting position. Focus on using your inner thigh muscles throughout the movement and maintain proper form to maximize the effectiveness of the exercise.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Hip Thrust (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "hipThrustBarbell", name: "Hip Thrust (Barbell)", description: "To perform hip thrusts with a barbell, start by sitting on the ground with your upper back against a sturdy bench or elevated surface. Position a barbell across your hips and roll it over your thighs until it is positioned directly above your hip joints. Keep your feet planted firmly on the ground, hip-width apart, and your knees bent at a 90-degree angle. Push through your heels and thrust your hips upward until your torso forms a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. Squeeze your glutes at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your hips back down to the starting position. Focus on contracting your glutes throughout the exercise and maintain stability to avoid arching your lower back excessively. Adjust the weight of the barbell as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Hip Thrust (Bodyweight)
    Exercise(id: "hipThrustBodyweight", name: "Hip Thrust (Bodyweight)", description: "To perform hip thrusts, start by sitting on the ground with your upper back against a sturdy bench or elevated surface. Place a barbell across your hips and roll it over your thighs until it's directly above your hip joints. Plant your feet firmly on the ground, shoulder-width apart, and bend your knees at a 90-degree angle. Push through your heels and thrust your hips upward until your torso forms a straight line from your knees to your shoulders. Squeeze your glutes at the top of the movement, then lower your hips back down in a controlled manner. Focus on engaging your glutes throughout the exercise and maintaining stability to avoid excessive arching of your lower back. Adjust the weight of the barbell as needed to suit your strength and fitness level.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Incline Bench Press (Dumbbell)
    Exercise(id: "inclineBenchPressDumbbell", name: "Incline Bench Press (Dumbbell)", description: "Adjust an incline bench to a 30-45 degree angle and sit on it with dumbbells resting on your thighs. Lie back on the bench and bring the dumbbells to shoulder height, palms facing forward. Press the dumbbells upward until your arms are fully extended, exhaling as you push. Lower the dumbbells back down to shoulder level in a controlled manner, inhaling as you return to the starting position. Keep your elbows slightly bent throughout the movement to maintain tension in your chest muscles. Focus on engaging your chest and stabilizing your shoulders throughout the exercise to maximize effectiveness.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .dumbbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Incline Chest Press (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "inclineChestPressMachine", name: "Incline Chest Press (Machine)", description: "Adjust the seat and backrest of the incline bench press machine to align with your body. Sit down on the machine with your back against the backrest and grasp the handles or grips provided. Push the handles forward to lift the weight stack or attach the appropriate amount of weight to the machine. Position your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and press the handles upward until your arms are fully extended. Lower the handles back down under control, allowing your elbows to bend to about 90 degrees. Focus on maintaining proper form and control throughout the exercise to effectively target your chest muscles. Adjust the seat and handle position as needed to ensure a comfortable and efficient range of motion.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Incline Curl (Dumbbell)
    Exercise(id: "inclineCurlDumbbell", name: "Incline Curl (Dumbbell)", description: "Set an incline bench to a comfortable angle (usually around 45 degrees) and sit on it with a dumbbell in each hand, arms hanging straight down toward the floor and palms facing forward. Keep your back against the bench and core engaged. Start with your elbows fully extended and curl the dumbbells upward toward your shoulders, keeping your upper arms stationary. Squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position with control. Focus on maintaining tension in your biceps throughout the exercise and avoid swinging the weights to ensure proper isolation and muscle engagement.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .dumbbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Incline Row (Dumbbell)
    Exercise(id: "inclineRowDumbbell", name: "Incline Row (Dumbbell)", description: "Set an incline bench to a 45-degree angle and lie face down on it with a dumbbell in each hand, arms hanging straight down toward the floor and palms facing each other. Keep your chest against the bench and core engaged. Start with your elbows fully extended and pull the dumbbells upward toward your rib cage, squeezing your shoulder blades together at the top of the movement. Lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position in a controlled manner. Focus on keeping your elbows close to your body and using your back muscles (especially your lats) to perform the rowing motion effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .dumbbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Iso-Lateral Chest Press (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "isoLateralChestPressMachine", name: "Iso-Lateral Chest Press (Machine)", description: "Adjust the seat and handles or grips of the iso-lateral chest press machine to align with your body. Sit down on the machine and grasp the handles with palms facing forward. Push the handles forward to lift the weight stack or attach the appropriate amount of weight to the machine. Position your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and press the handles forward until your arms are fully extended. Keep your elbows slightly bent to maintain tension in your chest muscles throughout the exercise. Slowly bring the handles back to the starting position, maintaining control of the movement. Focus on squeezing your chest muscles at the end of each press to maximize muscle engagement. Adjust the seat and handle position as needed to ensure a comfortable and effective range of motion for your body.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Iso-Lateral Row (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "isoLateralRowMachine", name: "Iso-Lateral Row (Machine)", description: "Adjust the seat and handles of the iso-lateral row machine to fit your body comfortably. Sit down on the machine and grasp the handles with an overhand grip, palms facing downward. Keep your back straight, chest up, and core engaged throughout the exercise. Pull the handles toward your torso by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together. Pause briefly at the end of the movement, then slowly extend your arms to return to the starting position. Focus on using your back muscles (especially your lats) to perform the rowing motion and maintain control of the weight throughout the exercise. Adjust the machine settings and handle position as needed to achieve a full range of motion and maximize muscle engagement.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Lat Pulldown (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "latPulldownMachine", name: "Lat Pulldown (Machine)", description: "Adjust the seat and knee pads of the lat pulldown machine to fit your body size. Sit down on the machine and grasp the wide bar attachment with an overhand grip, hands wider than shoulder-width apart. Lean back slightly and pull the bar down toward your chest by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together. Keep your chest up and avoid using momentum to pull the weight down. Pause briefly when the bar is close to your chest, then slowly extend your arms to return to the starting position. Focus on using your latissimus dorsi muscles (lats) to perform the pulldown movement and maintain control throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight and machine settings as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Lat Pulldown (Cable)
    Exercise(id: "latPulldownCable", name: "Lat Pulldown (Cable)", description: "Set the cable machine pulley to a high position and attach a wide bar or handle. Stand or kneel facing the machine with feet shoulder-width apart. Grasp the bar or handle with an overhand grip, hands wider than shoulder-width apart. Lean back slightly and pull the bar down toward your chest by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together. Keep your chest up and core engaged throughout the exercise. Pause briefly when the bar is close to your chest, then slowly extend your arms to return to the starting position. Focus on using your lats to perform the pulldown movement and maintain tension in the cable throughout the exercise for resistance. Adjust the weight and cable position as needed to accommodate your strength and range of motion.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Lat Pulldown (Single Arm)
    Exercise(id: "latPulldownSingleArm", name: "Lat Pulldown (Single Arm)", description: "Begin by setting the cable machine's pulley to a high position and attaching a single handle or rope. Stand facing the machine with feet shoulder-width apart. Grab the handle with one hand using an overhand grip. Keep your torso upright and engage your core for stability. Pull the handle down toward your side by bending your elbow and squeezing your shoulder blade down and back. Pause briefly when your hand is near your side, then slowly extend your arm back to the starting position. Focus on using your latissimus dorsi muscle to perform the movement and maintain control throughout. Repeat on the other side after completing the desired number of repetitions.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Lateral Raise (Band)
    Exercise(id: "lateralRaiseBand", name: "Lateral Raise (Band)", description: "Stand on the middle of a resistance band with feet shoulder-width apart. Grasp the handles or ends of the band with palms facing inward and arms by your sides. Keep a slight bend in your elbows throughout the exercise. Raise both arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor, maintaining control and focusing on using your shoulder muscles (deltoids). Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your arms back to the starting position. Keep tension in the band throughout the exercise to maximize resistance and muscle engagement in your shoulders.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .resistanceBand, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Lateral Raise (Cable)
    Exercise(id: "lateralRaiseCable", name: "Lateral Raise (Cable)", description: "Set the cable machine pulley to a low position and attach a handle or rope. Stand sideways to the machine with feet shoulder-width apart. Grasp the handle or rope with the hand closest to the machine using an overhand grip. Keep a slight bend in your elbow and your torso upright. Raise your arm out to the side until it is parallel to the floor, maintaining control and focusing on using your deltoid muscles. Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then slowly lower your arm back to the starting position. Maintain tension in the cable throughout the exercise to ensure continuous resistance and effective muscle engagement in your shoulders. Adjust the weight and cable position as needed to suit your strength and range of motion.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Lateral Raise (Dumbbell)
    Exercise(id: "lateralRaiseDumbbell", name: "Lateral Raise (Dumbbell)", description: "Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides with palms facing inward. Keep a slight bend in your elbows throughout the exercise. Raise both arms out to the sides until they are parallel to the floor, focusing on using your shoulder muscles (deltoids) to lift the dumbbells. Avoid swinging your arms and maintain control throughout the movement. Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the dumbbells back to the starting position. Keep tension in your shoulders throughout the exercise to maximize muscle engagement and effectiveness.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .dumbbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Lateral Raise (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "lateralRaiseMachine", name: "Lateral Raise (Machine)", description: "Adjust the seat and handles of the lateral raise machine to fit your body size. Sit down on the machine and grasp the handles with palms facing inward. Keep your back straight and chest up throughout the exercise. Lift the handles out to the sides until your arms are parallel to the floor, focusing on using your deltoid muscles to perform the movement. Avoid using momentum and maintain control as you lower the handles back to the starting position. Adjust the weight and machine settings as needed to achieve a full range of motion and effectively target your shoulder muscles.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Leg Extension (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "legExtensionMachine", name: "Leg Extension (Machine)", description: "Adjust the seat and backrest of the leg extension machine to fit your body size. Sit down on the machine with your back against the backrest and place your shins under the padded lever or roller. Adjust the lever or roller so that it rests just above your ankles. Grasp the handles provided for stability and straighten your legs to lift the weight until your legs are almost fully extended. Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the weight back down to the starting position, maintaining control throughout. Focus on using your quadriceps muscles to extend your knees and avoid swinging your legs to maximize muscle engagement and effectiveness. Adjust the weight and machine settings as needed to challenge your muscles appropriately.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Leg Curl (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "legCurlMachine", name: "Leg Curl (Machine)", description: "Adjust the machine's settings to fit your body size, ensuring the padded lever is positioned just above your ankles. Lie face down on the machine with your legs straight and the backs of your ankles against the padded lever. Grasp the handles or hold onto the machine for stability. Contract your hamstrings to pull the lever upward toward your glutes, bending your knees. Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the lever back down to the starting position under control. Focus on using your hamstrings to perform the curling motion and avoid arching your back. Adjust the weight and machine settings as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Leg Press (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "legPressMachine", name: "Leg Press (Machine)", description: "Adjust the seat and footplate of the leg press machine to fit your body size. Sit down on the machine and place your feet shoulder-width apart on the footplate with your knees bent. Grasp the handles provided for stability. Press the footplate away from your body by extending your knees and hips until your legs are almost fully extended, but without locking your knees. Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then slowly bend your knees to lower the footplate back toward your body in a controlled manner. Focus on using your quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes to perform the pressing motion and maintain proper form throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight and machine settings as needed to suit your strength and range of motion.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Lunge (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "lungeBarbell", name: "Lunge (Barbell)", description: "Start by standing with your feet hip-width apart and a barbell across your upper back, gripping it with an overhand grip. Take a large step forward with one foot and lower your body by bending both knees until your front thigh is parallel to the ground and your back knee is just above the floor. Keep your torso upright and core engaged throughout the movement. Push through your front heel to return to the starting position, bringing your back foot forward to meet the front foot. Repeat the movement on the opposite leg. Focus on maintaining balance and control throughout the exercise, keeping your front knee aligned with your ankle and not extending past your toes. Adjust the weight of the barbell as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Lunge (Dumbbell)
    Exercise(id: "lungeDumbbell", name: "Lunge (Dumbbell)", description: "Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at your sides. Take a large step forward with one foot and lower your body by bending both knees until your front thigh is parallel to the ground and your back knee is just above the floor. Keep your torso upright and core engaged throughout the movement. Push through your front heel to return to the starting position, bringing your back foot forward to meet the front foot. Repeat the movement on the opposite leg. Focus on maintaining balance and control throughout the exercise, ensuring your front knee stays aligned with your ankle and does not extend past your toes. Adjust the weight of the dumbbells as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Lying Leg Curl
    Exercise(id: "lungeDumbbell", name: "Lunge (Dumbbell)", description: "Adjust the machine settings to fit your body size, ensuring the padded lever is positioned just above your heels. Lie face down on the machine with your legs straight and the backs of your ankles against the padded lever. Grasp the handles or hold onto the machine for stability. Contract your hamstrings to pull the lever upward toward your glutes, bending your knees. Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then slowly lower the lever back down to the starting position under control. Focus on using your hamstrings to perform the curling motion and maintain proper form throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight and machine settings as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Military Press (Kettlebell)
    Exercise(id: "militaryPressKettlebell", name: "Military Press (Kettlebell)", description: "Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell by the handle with both hands at shoulder height. Engage your core and keep your back straight throughout the exercise. Press the kettlebell overhead by extending your arms fully, pushing the weight toward the ceiling. Lower the kettlebell back down to shoulder height with control, bending your elbows slightly as you bring it down. Focus on using your shoulder muscles to perform the pressing motion and maintain stability throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight of the kettlebell as needed to suit your strength and fitness level.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .kettlebell, executionType: .setsReps),

    // Overhead Tricep Extension (Dumbbell)
    Exercise(id: "overheadTricepExtensionDumbbell", name: "Overhead Tricep Extension (Dumbbell)", description: "Start by standing or sitting with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell with both hands. Raise the dumbbell overhead, keeping your elbows close to your ears and your palms facing upward. Lower the dumbbell behind your head by bending your elbows, allowing them to move backward. Keep your upper arms stationary throughout the movement. Extend your elbows to lift the dumbbell back to the starting position, fully extending your arms without locking your elbows at the top. Focus on contracting your triceps throughout the exercise and maintain control over the weight to avoid strain.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .dumbbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Overhead Press (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "overheadPressBarbell", name: "Overhead Press (Barbell)", description: "Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, gripping a barbell with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Lift the barbell to shoulder height, resting it on your upper chest with elbows bent and palms facing forward. Engage your core and keep your back straight throughout the exercise. Press the barbell upward until your arms are fully extended overhead, exhaling as you push. Lower the barbell back down to shoulder height in a controlled manner, inhaling as you return to the starting position. Focus on using your shoulder muscles to perform the pressing motion and maintain stability throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight of the barbell as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Overhead Press (Cable)
    Exercise(id: "overheadPressCable", name: "Overhead Press (Cable)", description: "Set the cable machine's pulley to a high position and attach a straight bar or handle. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, facing away from the machine. Grasp the bar or handle with an overhand grip, hands wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your elbows slightly bent and the bar at shoulder height. Press the bar overhead by extending your arms fully, pushing the weight away from your body. Control the bar as you lower it back down to shoulder height, keeping tension on the cable throughout the exercise. Focus on using your shoulder muscles to perform the pressing motion and maintain proper form throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight and cable position as needed to suit your strength and range of motion.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Overhead Press (Dumbbell)
    Exercise(id: "overheadPressDumbbell", name: "Overhead Press (Dumbbell)", description: "Begin by sitting or standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height. Keep your elbows bent and palms facing forward. Engage your core and keep your back straight throughout the exercise. Press the dumbbells overhead by extending your arms fully, exhaling as you push. Keep your wrists straight and avoid locking your elbows at the top of the movement. Lower the dumbbells back down to shoulder height in a controlled manner, inhaling as you return to the starting position. Focus on using your shoulder muscles to perform the pressing motion and maintain stability throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight of the dumbbells as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .dumbbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Overhead Press (Smith Machine)
    Exercise(id: "overheadPressSmithMachine", name: "Overhead Press (Smith Machine)", description: "Adjust the barbell on the Smith machine to a height that allows you to comfortably press it overhead while standing. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart under the barbell, gripping it with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Engage your core and keep your back straight throughout the exercise. Press the barbell overhead by extending your arms fully, exhaling as you push. Lower the barbell back down to shoulder height in a controlled manner, inhaling as you return to the starting position. Focus on using your shoulder muscles to perform the pressing motion and maintain stability throughout the exercise. The Smith machine provides a guided path for the barbell, helping you maintain proper form.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Overhead Squat (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "overheadSquatBarbell", name: "Overhead Squat (Barbell)", description: "Start by standing with your feet hip-width apart and the barbell positioned across your upper back, gripping it with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Engage your core and keep your chest up throughout the exercise. Squat down by bending your knees and pushing your hips back, maintaining the barbell overhead. Keep your arms extended and elbows locked throughout the movement. Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as low as your flexibility allows. Push through your heels to return to the starting position, keeping the barbell overhead throughout. Focus on maintaining balance and control throughout the exercise, keeping your chest up and knees tracking over your toes. Adjust the weight of the barbell as needed to challenge your leg muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Pec Deck (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "pecDeckMachine", name: "Pec Deck (Machine)", description: "Adjust the seat and handles of the pec deck machine to fit your body size. Sit down with your back against the backrest and grasp the handles with an overhand grip. Keep your upper arms parallel to the floor throughout the exercise. Press the handles together in front of your chest by squeezing your pecs (chest muscles). Hold the contraction briefly, then slowly release the handles back to the starting position. Focus on using your chest muscles to control the movement and maintain a smooth, controlled pace. Adjust the weight on the machine as needed to suit your strength and fitness level.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Pendlay Row (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "pendlayRowBarbell", name: "Pendlay Row (Barbell)", description: "Start by standing with your feet hip-width apart and a barbell on the floor in front of you. Bend at your hips and knees to grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back flat, chest up, and core engaged throughout the exercise. Lift the barbell off the floor by extending your hips and knees, keeping your arms fully extended. Pull the barbell toward your lower chest or upper abdomen by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together. Lower the barbell back to the floor under control to complete one repetition. Focus on using your back muscles (especially your lats) to perform the rowing motion and maintain proper form. Adjust the weight of the barbell as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Power Clean (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "powerCleanBarbell", name: "Power Clean (Barbell)", description: "Start with the barbell on the floor in front of you, feet hip-width apart and toes pointing slightly outward. Bend at your hips and knees to grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back flat, chest up, and core engaged. Lift the barbell off the floor explosively by extending your hips, knees, and ankles, pulling the barbell upward. As the barbell reaches hip level, quickly drop underneath it by bending your elbows and catching the barbell at shoulder height in a front squat position. Stand up straight to complete the movement, then lower the barbell back to the floor under control. Focus on generating power from your lower body and maintaining a smooth, fluid motion throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight of the barbell as needed to perform the exercise with proper technique and intensity.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Power Snatch (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "powerSnatchBarbell", name: "Power Snatch (Barbell)", description: "Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart and a barbell on the floor in front of you. Bend at your hips and knees to grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back flat, chest up, and core engaged throughout the exercise. Lift the barbell off the floor explosively by extending your hips, knees, and ankles, pulling the barbell upward. As the barbell reaches hip level, continue pulling it upward by bending your elbows and bringing the barbell overhead in one smooth motion. Drop underneath the barbell into a partial squat position, catching it overhead with fully extended arms. Stand up straight to complete the movement, then lower the barbell back to the floor under control. Focus on generating power from your lower body and maintaining a smooth, fluid motion throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight of the barbell as needed to perform the exercise with proper technique and intensity.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Pullover (Dumbbell)
    Exercise(id: "pulloverDumbbell", name: "Pullover (Dumbbell)", description: "Lie down on a bench with your upper back supported and feet flat on the floor. Grip a barbell with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart, and hold it above your chest with arms fully extended. Keep a slight bend in your elbows throughout the exercise. Lower the barbell behind your head in a smooth arc motion, maintaining control and stretching your lats (back muscles) and chest. Pause briefly when the barbell is parallel to the floor or when you feel a stretch in your muscles. Lift the barbell back to the starting position by contracting your lats and chest muscles. Focus on maintaining stability on the bench and controlling the movement to maximize muscle engagement.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .dumbbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Pullover (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "pulloverMachine", name: "Pullover (Machine)", description: "Adjust the seat and handles of the pullover machine to fit your body size. Sit down with your back against the backrest and grasp the handles or bar with an overhand grip. Keep your arms slightly bent and maintain a firm grip on the handles throughout the exercise. Extend your arms overhead in a controlled manner, allowing the handles to move toward the floor and stretching your lats (back muscles). Pause briefly when your arms are extended and you feel a stretch in your muscles. Contract your lats and chest muscles to pull the handles back to the starting position. Focus on using your back muscles to control the movement and maintain proper form throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight on the machine as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Push Press (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "pushPressBarbell", name: "Push Press (Barbell)", description: "Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and a barbell resting on your upper chest, gripping it with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Bend your knees slightly and engage your core. Dip down by bending your knees and hips, then explosively drive through your legs to generate upward momentum. As you extend your legs, press the barbell overhead by fully extending your arms. Use the momentum from your lower body to assist with lifting the weight overhead. Lower the barbell back to your upper chest in a controlled manner to complete one repetition. Focus on maintaining stability and control throughout the exercise, keeping your core engaged and avoiding excessive arching of your lower back.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Rack Pull (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "rackPullBarbell", name: "Rack Pull (Barbell)", description: "Set up a barbell on a rack at knee height or slightly above, ensuring it is positioned securely. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and approach the barbell. Grip the barbell with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back straight, chest up, and core engaged throughout the exercise. Lift the barbell by extending your hips and knees, pulling your shoulders back and squeezing your shoulder blades together. Keep the barbell close to your body throughout the movement. Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then lower the barbell back down to the rack in a controlled manner. Focus on using your hip and back muscles to perform the movement and maintain proper form. Adjust the weight on the barbell as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Romanian Deadlift (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "romanianDeadliftBarbell", name: "Romanian Deadlift (Barbell)", description: "Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart and a barbell in front of you on the floor. Bend at your hips and knees to grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back flat, chest up, and core engaged throughout the exercise. Lift the barbell off the floor by extending your hips and knees until you are standing upright. Maintain a slight bend in your knees throughout the movement. Lower the barbell by pushing your hips back and bending at the hips while keeping your back straight. Lower the barbell until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings (back of thighs), then return to the starting position by squeezing your glutes and extending your hips forward. Focus on maintaining tension in your hamstrings and avoiding rounding your back throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight of the barbell as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Romanian Deadlift (Dumbbell)
    Exercise(id: "romanianDeadliftDumbbell", name: "Romanian Deadlift (Dumbbell)", description: "Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand in front of your thighs with palms facing your body. Engage your core and keep your back flat throughout the exercise. Hinge at your hips, pushing your hips back while maintaining a slight bend in your knees. Lower the dumbbells along the front of your legs, keeping them close to your body. Lower until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings (back of thighs), ensuring your back remains straight. Avoid rounding your back. Pause briefly at the bottom of the movement, then return to the starting position by driving through your heels and squeezing your glutes. Focus on maintaining control and tension in your hamstrings throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight of the dumbbells as needed to suit your strength and fitness level.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .dumbbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Seated Calf Raise (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "seatedCalfRaiseMachine", name: "Seated Calf Raise (Machine)", description: "Adjust the seat and weight stack of the seated calf raise machine to fit your body size. Sit down and place your toes on the platform with the balls of your feet and arches securely positioned. Adjust the seat and back pad so your knees are slightly bent and the balls of your feet are on the platform. Grasp the handles or hold onto the machine for stability. Lift the weight by extending your ankles and raising your heels as high as possible. Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then lower your heels back down to the starting position in a controlled manner. Focus on squeezing your calf muscles throughout the movement and maintaining a steady pace. Adjust the weight on the machine as needed to challenge your calf muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Seated Calf Raise (Plate Loaded)
    Exercise(id: "seatedCalfRaisePlateLoaded", name: "Seated Calf Raise (Plate Loaded)", description: "Sit on a seated calf raise machine with your knees bent and your shoulders under the pads. Place your toes on the foot platform with your heels hanging off. Grasp the handles or hold onto the machine for stability. Push through the balls of your feet to raise the weight, extending your ankles and lifting your heels as high as possible. Hold the contraction briefly at the top of the movement, then lower your heels back down to the starting position under control. Focus on squeezing your calf muscles throughout the exercise and maintaining proper form. Adjust the weight plates loaded on the machine as needed to suit your strength and fitness level.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Seated Leg Curl (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "seatedLegCurlMachine", name: "Seated Leg Curl (Machine)", description: "Adjust the machine to fit your body size, ensuring the padded lever is positioned just above your heels. Sit on the machine with your back against the backrest and place your lower legs under the padded lever. Grasp the handles or hold onto the machine for stability. Keep your thighs flat against the thigh pad throughout the exercise. Contract your hamstrings to pull the padded lever toward your glutes, bending your knees. Hold the contraction briefly, then slowly lower the lever back to the starting position under control. Focus on using your hamstrings to perform the curling motion and maintain proper form throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight on the machine as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Seated Overhead Press (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "seatedOverheadPressBarbell", name: "Seated Overhead Press (Barbell)", description: "Begin by sitting on a bench with back support or on a chair with your feet flat on the floor. Grip a barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Lift the barbell to shoulder height, resting it on your upper chest with elbows bent. Engage your core and keep your back straight throughout the exercise. Press the barbell overhead by extending your arms fully, exhaling as you push. Lower the barbell back to shoulder height in a controlled manner, inhaling as you return to the starting position. Focus on using your shoulder muscles to perform the pressing motion and maintain stability throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight of the barbell as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Seated Overhead Press (Dumbbell)
    Exercise(id: "seatedOverheadPressDumbbell", name: "Seated Overhead Press (Dumbbell)", description: "Start by sitting on a bench with back support or on a chair with your feet flat on the floor. Hold a dumbbell in each hand at shoulder height, palms facing forward and elbows bent. Engage your core and keep your back straight throughout the exercise. Press the dumbbells overhead by extending your arms fully, exhaling as you push. Keep your wrists straight and avoid locking your elbows at the top of the movement. Lower the dumbbells back to shoulder height in a controlled manner, inhaling as you return to the starting position. Focus on using your shoulder muscles to perform the pressing motion and maintain stability throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight of the dumbbells as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .dumbbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Seated Palms Up Wrist Curl (Dumbbell)
    Exercise(id: "seatedPalmsUpWristCurlDumbbell", name: "Seated Palms Up Wrist Curl (Dumbbell)", description: "Sit on a bench with your forearms resting on your thighs and a dumbbell in each hand, palms facing upward. Allow your wrists to extend beyond your knees with your palms up. Flex your wrists to lift the dumbbells as high as possible, keeping your forearms on your thighs. Hold the top position briefly, then slowly lower the dumbbells back down until your wrists are fully extended. Focus on using your forearm muscles to perform the wrist curl motion and maintain control throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight of the dumbbells as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .dumbbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Seated Row (Cable)
    Exercise(id: "seatedRowCable", name: "Seated Row (Cable)", description: "Sit on a bench facing a cable machine with a straight bar attached to the low pulley. Adjust the weight stack and seat height so that the bar is at arm's length. Grasp the bar with an overhand grip slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back straight, chest up, and core engaged throughout the exercise. Pull the bar toward your lower chest by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together. Pause briefly at the fully contracted position, then slowly extend your arms to lower the bar back to the starting position under control. Focus on using your back muscles (especially your lats) to perform the rowing motion and maintain proper form. Adjust the weight on the cable machine as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Seated Row (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "seatedRowMachine", name: "Seated Row (Machine)", description: "Adjust the seat and handles of the seated row machine to fit your body size. Sit down with your back against the backrest and grasp the handles with an overhand grip. Keep your chest up and core engaged throughout the exercise. Pull the handles toward your lower chest by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together. Hold the contraction briefly, then slowly extend your arms to return to the starting position in a controlled manner. Focus on using your back muscles (especially your lats) to perform the rowing motion and maintain proper form throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight on the machine as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Seated Wide-Grip Row (Cable)
    Exercise(id: "seatedWideGripRowCable", name: "Seated Wide-Grip Row (Cable)", description: "Sit on a bench facing a cable machine with a straight bar attached to the low pulley. Adjust the weight stack and seat height so that the bar is at arm's length. Grasp the bar with a wider than shoulder-width grip, palms facing down. Keep your back straight, chest up, and core engaged throughout the exercise. Pull the bar toward your lower chest by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together. Pause briefly at the fully contracted position, then slowly extend your arms to lower the bar back to the starting position under control. Focus on using your back muscles (especially your lats) to perform the rowing motion and maintain proper form. Adjust the weight on the cable machine as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Shoulder Press (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "shoulderPressMachine", name: "Shoulder Press (Machine)", description: "Adjust the seat and handles of the shoulder press machine to fit your body size. Sit down with your back against the backrest and grasp the handles or grips with an overhand grip. Keep your feet flat on the floor and your back straight throughout the exercise. Press the handles or grips overhead by extending your arms fully, exhaling as you push. Lower the handles or grips back to shoulder height in a controlled manner, inhaling as you return to the starting position. Focus on using your shoulder muscles to perform the pressing motion and maintain stability throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight on the machine as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Shoulder Press (Plate Loaded)
    Exercise(id: "shoulderPressPlateLoaded", name: "Shoulder Press (Plate Loaded)", description: "Grip the handles of the plate loaded shoulder press machine with an overhand grip. Lift the weight plates to shoulder height, resting them on your upper chest with elbows bent. Engage your core and keep your back straight throughout the exercise. Press the weight plates overhead by extending your arms fully, exhaling as you push. Lower the weight plates back to shoulder height in a controlled manner, inhaling as you return to the starting position. Focus on using your shoulder muscles to perform the pressing motion and maintain stability throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight plates loaded on the machine as needed to suit your strength and fitness level.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Shrug (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "shrugBarbell", name: "Shrug (Barbell)", description: "Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and a barbell held in front of your thighs with an overhand grip, hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your arms fully extended throughout the exercise. Lift your shoulders toward your ears as high as possible while keeping your arms straight. Hold the top position briefly to maximize the contraction in your trapezius muscles. Lower your shoulders back down in a controlled manner to complete one repetition. Focus on using your traps to lift the weight and avoid using momentum or swinging the barbell.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Shrug (Dumbbell)
    Exercise(id: "shrugDumbbell", name: "Shrug (Dumbbell)", description: "Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and hold a dumbbell in each hand by your sides with your palms facing your body. Keep your arms fully extended throughout the exercise. Lift your shoulders toward your ears as high as possible while keeping your arms straight. Hold the top position briefly to maximize the contraction in your traps. Lower your shoulders back down in a controlled manner to complete one repetition. Focus on using your traps to lift the weights and maintain a stable stance throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight of the dumbbells as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .dumbbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Skullcrusher (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "skullcrusherBarbell", name: "Skullcrusher (Barbell)", description: "Lie down on a bench with your back flat and hold a barbell with an overhand grip, hands slightly closer than shoulder-width apart. Extend your arms straight up toward the ceiling, keeping your elbows stationary throughout the exercise. Lower the barbell toward your forehead by bending your elbows, allowing them to move backward slightly. Keep your upper arms perpendicular to the floor. Pause briefly when the barbell is near your forehead, then extend your elbows to lift the barbell back to the starting position. Focus on using your triceps to control the movement and avoid arching your back. Adjust the weight on the barbell as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Skullcrusher (Dumbbell)
    Exercise(id: "skullcrusherDumbbell", name: "Skullcrusher (Dumbbell)", description: "Start by lying on a bench with your back flat and holding a dumbbell in each hand above your chest with palms facing inward. Extend your arms straight up toward the ceiling, keeping your elbows stationary throughout the exercise. Lower the dumbbells toward your forehead by bending your elbows, allowing them to move backward slightly. Keep your upper arms perpendicular to the floor. Pause briefly when the dumbbells are near your forehead, then extend your elbows to lift the dumbbells back to the starting position. Focus on using your triceps to control the movement and maintain stability throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight of the dumbbells as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .dumbbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Snatch (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "snatchBarbell", name: "Snatch (Barbell)", description: "Stand with your feet hip-width apart and a barbell on the floor in front of you. Bend at your hips and knees to grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, hands wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back flat, chest up, and core engaged throughout the exercise. Lift the barbell off the floor explosively by extending your hips, knees, and ankles, pulling the barbell upward. As the barbell reaches hip level, continue pulling it upward by bending your elbows and bringing the barbell overhead in one smooth motion. Drop underneath the barbell into a partial squat position, catching it overhead with fully extended arms. Stand up straight to complete the movement, then lower the barbell back to the floor under control. Focus on generating power from your lower body and maintaining a smooth, fluid motion throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight of the barbell as needed to perform the exercise with proper technique and intensity.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Snatch Pull (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "snatchPullBarbell", name: "Snatch Pull (Barbell)", description: "Start by standing with your feet hip-width apart and a barbell on the floor in front of you. Bend at your hips and knees to grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, hands wider than shoulder-width apart. Keep your back flat, chest up, and core engaged throughout the exercise. Lift the barbell off the floor explosively by extending your hips, knees, and ankles, pulling the barbell upward. As the barbell reaches hip level, continue pulling it upward by driving your elbows high and keeping the barbell close to your body. Stand up straight and shrug your shoulders at the top of the movement to maximize the height of the barbell. Lower the barbell back to the floor under control to complete one repetition. Focus on using your lower body and back muscles to generate power and maintain proper form throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight of the barbell as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Split Jerk (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "splitJerkBarbell", name: "Split Jerk (Barbell)", description: "Begin by standing with your feet hip-width apart and a barbell on your upper chest, hands positioned slightly wider than shoulder-width apart with an overhand grip. Bend your knees slightly and engage your core. Dip down by bending your knees and hips, then explosively drive through your legs to generate upward momentum. As you extend your legs, press the barbell overhead by fully extending your arms. At the same time, split your legs into a staggered stance, one foot forward and one foot back. Lower your body into a partial squat position to catch the barbell overhead with your arms fully extended. Stand up straight to complete the movement, then return to the starting position by bringing your front foot back and lowering the barbell under control. Focus on coordinating the movement of your lower body and arms to execute the split jerk smoothly and with stability.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Squat (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "squatBarbell", name: "Squat (Barbell)", description: "Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and a barbell on your upper back, resting comfortably across your trapezius muscles (high bar position) or lower on your back (low bar position). Grip the barbell with your hands wider than shoulder-width apart, palms facing forward. Engage your core, keep your chest up, and maintain a slight arch in your lower back throughout the exercise. Bend your knees and hips to lower your body into a squat position, keeping your knees in line with your toes. Lower yourself until your thighs are at least parallel to the floor or as far as comfortably possible. Push through your heels and midfoot to stand back up, extending your knees and hips until you're back at the starting position. Focus on maintaining proper form, keeping your chest lifted and avoiding rounding your back.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Squat (Dumbbell)
    Exercise(id: "squatDumbbell", name: "Squat (Dumbbell)", description: "Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand by your sides with palms facing inward. Engage your core and keep your chest up throughout the exercise. Position the dumbbells at shoulder height, with your elbows bent and palms facing forward. Bend your knees and hips to lower your body into a squat position, keeping your knees in line with your toes. Lower yourself until your thighs are at least parallel to the floor or as far as comfortably possible. Push through your heels and midfoot to stand back up, extending your knees and hips until you're back at the starting position. Focus on maintaining proper form, keeping your chest lifted and avoiding rounding your back. Adjust the weight of the dumbbells as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .dumbbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Squat (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "squatMachine", name: "Squat (Machine)", description: "Adjust the seat and foot platform of the squat machine to fit your body size. Position yourself under the shoulder pads and place your feet shoulder-width apart on the platform. Engage your core and keep your back against the backrest throughout the exercise. Unrack the weight by straightening your legs and lifting the safety bars. Bend your knees and hips to lower yourself into a squat position, keeping your back straight and knees in line with your toes. Lower yourself until your thighs are at least parallel to the floor or as far as comfortably possible. Push through your heels and midfoot to stand back up, extending your knees and hips until you're back at the starting position. Focus on maintaining proper alignment and control throughout the movement. Adjust the weight on the machine as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Standing Calf Raise (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "standingCalfRaiseBarbell", name: "Standing Calf Raise (Barbell)", description: "Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and a barbell on your upper back, resting comfortably across your trapezius muscles. Grip the barbell with your hands wider than shoulder-width apart, palms facing forward. Engage your core and keep your chest up throughout the exercise. Rise onto the balls of your feet by lifting your heels as high as possible. Hold the top position briefly to maximize the contraction in your calf muscles. Lower your heels back down in a controlled manner to complete one repetition. Focus on using your calf muscles to perform the lifting motion and maintain stability throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight on the barbell as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Standing Calf Raise (Bodyweight)
    Exercise(id: "standingCalfRaiseBodyweight", name: "Standing Calf Raise (Bodyweight)", description: "Stand upright with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands on your hips or lightly touching a stable surface for balance. Lift your heels off the ground by pushing through the balls of your feet, rising as high as possible onto your tiptoes. Hold the top position briefly to maximize the contraction in your calf muscles. Lower your heels back down slowly and with control to complete one repetition. Focus on using your calf muscles to perform the lifting motion and maintain stability throughout the exercise. Perform the exercise on a flat, stable surface to ensure safety and proper form. Adjust the tempo and repetitions to suit your fitness level and goals.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Stiff Leg Deadlift (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "stiffLegDeadliftBarbell", name: "Stiff Leg Deadlift (Barbell)", description: "Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a barbell in front of your thighs with palms facing your body. Keep your knees slightly bent, back flat, chest up, and core engaged throughout the exercise. Hinge at your hips and lower the barbell toward the floor, keeping them close to your body. Lower until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings while maintaining a slight bend in your knees. Pause briefly at the bottom, then return to the starting position by squeezing your hamstrings and glutes, and standing upright. Focus on maintaining a controlled motion and feeling the stretch in your hamstrings throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight of the barbell as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Stiff Leg Deadlift (Dumbbell)
    Exercise(id: "stiffLegDeadliftDumbbell", name: "Stiff Leg Deadlift (Dumbbell)", description: "Stand with your feet hip-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand in front of your thighs with palms facing your body. Keep your knees slightly bent, back flat, chest up, and core engaged throughout the exercise. Hinge at your hips and lower the dumbbells toward the floor, keeping them close to your body. Lower until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings while maintaining a slight bend in your knees. Pause briefly at the bottom, then return to the starting position by squeezing your hamstrings and glutes, and standing upright. Focus on maintaining a controlled motion and feeling the stretch in your hamstrings throughout the exercise. Adjust the weight of the dumbbells as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .dumbbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Straight Leg Deadlift (Band)
    Exercise(id: "straightLegDeadliftBand", name: "Straight Leg Deadlift (Band)", description: "Start by standing on a resistance band with your feet shoulder-width apart or wider, holding one end of the band in each hand. Keep your knees slightly bent, back flat, chest up, and core engaged throughout the exercise. Hold the band with your palms facing your body and arms straight down in front of your thighs. Hinge at your hips and lower your torso forward, allowing the band to stretch naturally as you lower. Lower until you feel a stretch in your hamstrings while maintaining tension in the band. Pause briefly at the bottom, then return to the starting position by squeezing your hamstrings and glutes, and standing upright. Focus on maintaining tension in the resistance band throughout the exercise to engage your hamstrings effectively. Adjust the resistance band's tension by gripping closer to or farther from the ends as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .resistanceBand, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Sumo Deadlift (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "sumoDeadliftBarbell", name: "Sumo Deadlift (Barbell)", description: "Stand with your feet wider than shoulder-width apart and a barbell on the floor in front of you. Position your feet so that they are wider than shoulder-width apart with your toes pointed slightly outward. Bend at your hips and knees to grasp the barbell with an overhand grip, hands inside your legs. Keep your back flat, chest up, and core engaged throughout the exercise. Lift the barbell off the floor by extending your hips and knees until you're standing upright with the barbell in front of your thighs. Lower the barbell toward the floor by hinging at your hips and pushing them back while keeping your back straight. Lower the barbell as far as comfortably possible while maintaining the natural arch in your lower back. Pause briefly at the bottom, then return to the starting position by extending your hips and standing upright. Focus on using your hamstrings, glutes, and adductors to perform the movement and maintain proper form throughout.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Thruster (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "thrusterBarbell", name: "Thruster (Barbell)", description: "Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and a barbell held in front of your shoulders with an overhand grip. Keep your elbows up and chest up throughout the exercise. Bend your knees and hips to lower into a squat position, keeping your knees in line with your toes. Lower yourself until your thighs are at least parallel to the floor. Push through your heels and midfoot to stand back up explosively, simultaneously pressing the barbell overhead by extending your arms. Fully extend your arms overhead while you stand up straight to complete one repetition. Lower the barbell back to your shoulders under control as you lower back into the squat position to begin the next repetition. Focus on maintaining a fluid motion and generating power from your lower body to propel the barbell overhead. Adjust the weight on the barbell as needed to perform the exercise with proper technique and intensity.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Thruster (Kettlebell)
    Exercise(id: "thrusterKettlebell", name: "Thruster (Kettlebell)", description: "Begin by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a kettlebell in front of your chest with both hands, palms facing inward. Engage your core and keep your chest up throughout the exercise. Bend your knees and hips to lower into a squat position, keeping your knees in line with your toes. Lower yourself until your thighs are at least parallel to the floor. Push through your heels and midfoot to stand back up explosively, simultaneously pressing the kettlebell overhead by extending your arms. Fully extend your arms overhead while you stand up straight to complete one repetition. Lower the kettlebell back to your chest under control as you lower back into the squat position to begin the next repetition. Focus on maintaining a fluid motion and generating power from your lower body to propel the kettlebell overhead. Adjust the weight of the kettlebell as needed to perform the exercise with proper technique and intensity.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .kettlebell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Trap Bar Deadlift
    Exercise(id: "trapBarDeadlift", name: "Trap Bar Deadlift (Barbell)", description: "Stand inside a trap bar with your feet hip-width apart or slightly wider. Bend at your hips and knees to grasp the handles of the trap bar with an overhand grip. Keep your back flat, chest up, and core engaged throughout the exercise. Lift the trap bar off the ground by extending your hips and knees until you're standing upright with the trap bar at your sides. Maintain a neutral spine throughout the movement. Lower the trap bar back toward the ground by hinging at your hips and bending your knees. Lower the trap bar as far as comfortably possible while keeping your back straight. Pause briefly at the bottom, then return to the starting position by extending your hips and standing upright. Focus on using your hamstrings, glutes, and lower back muscles to perform the movement and maintain proper form throughout.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Triceps Extension (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "tricepsExtensionBarbell", name: "Triceps Extension (Barbell)", description: "Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and a barbell held overhead with an overhand grip, hands slightly closer than shoulder-width apart. Keep your elbows close to your head and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. Lower the barbell behind your head by bending your elbows, allowing them to move backward slightly. Keep your upper arms perpendicular to the floor. Pause briefly when the barbell is near your shoulders, then extend your elbows to lift the barbell back to the starting position. Focus on using your triceps to control the movement and avoid arching your back. Adjust the weight on the barbell as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Triceps Extension (Cable)
    Exercise(id: "tricepsExtensionCable", name: "Triceps Extension (Cable)", description: "Attach a straight or rope handle to the high pulley of a cable machine. Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, and grab the handle with an overhand grip. Position your elbows close to your head and your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. Extend your elbows to bring the handle down until your arms are fully extended. Keep your upper arms perpendicular to the floor. Pause briefly when your arms are fully extended, then bend your elbows to return to the starting position. Focus on using your triceps to control the movement and maintain a stable stance throughout. Adjust the weight on the cable machine to suit your strength and fitness level.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Upright Row (Barbell)
    Exercise(id: "uprightRowBarbell", name: "Upright Row (Barbell)", description: "Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and grasp a barbell with an overhand grip, hands closer than shoulder-width apart. Let the barbell hang in front of your thighs with your arms fully extended. Keep your chest up, back straight, and core engaged throughout the exercise. Lift the barbell upward by raising your elbows out to the sides and pulling the barbell toward your chin. Keep the barbell close to your body as you lift. Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then lower the barbell back to the starting position under control. Focus on using your shoulder and upper back muscles to perform the lifting motion and maintain proper form throughout. Adjust the weight on the barbell as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .barbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Upright Row (Cable)
    Exercise(id: "uprightRowCable", name: "Upright Row (Cable)", description: "Attach a straight or bar handle to the low pulley of a cable machine. Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, and grab the handle with an overhand grip. Keep your chest up, back straight, and core engaged throughout the exercise. Lift the handle upward by raising your elbows out to the sides and pulling the handle toward your chin. Keep the handle close to your body as you lift. Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then lower the handle back to the starting position under control. Focus on using your shoulder and upper back muscles to perform the lifting motion and maintain a stable stance throughout. Adjust the weight on the cable machine to suit your strength and fitness level.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Upright Row (Dumbbell)
    Exercise(id: "uprightRowDumbbell", name: "Upright Row (Dumbbell)", description: "Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a dumbbell in each hand with palms facing your body. Let your arms hang straight down in front of your thighs. Keep your chest up, back straight, and core engaged throughout the exercise. Lift the dumbbells upward by raising your elbows out to the sides and pulling them toward your chin. Keep the dumbbells close to your body as you lift. Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then lower the dumbbells back to the starting position under control. Focus on using your shoulder and upper back muscles to perform the lifting motion and maintain proper form throughout. Adjust the weight of the dumbbells as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .dumbbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Tricep Kickback (Dumbbell)
    Exercise(id: "tricepKickbackDumbbell", name: "Tricep Kickback (Dumbbell)", description: "Start by holding a dumbbell in each hand, standing with your feet hip-width apart. Bend your knees slightly and hinge forward at your hips, keeping your back flat and chest up. Position your elbows close to your sides at a 90-degree angle, with your upper arms parallel to the floor. Extend your elbows and straighten your arms backward until they are fully extended, squeezing your triceps at the top of the movement. Keep your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. Pause briefly at the top, then bend your elbows to return to the starting position. Focus on using your triceps to control the movement and maintain stability throughout. Adjust the weight of the dumbbells as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .dumbbell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Tricep Pressdown (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "tricepPressdownMachine", name: "Tricep Pressdown (Machine)", description: "Adjust the seat and weight stack on the tricep pressdown machine to fit your body size. Stand facing the machine with your feet shoulder-width apart, and grasp the handles with an overhand grip. Position your elbows close to your sides and bent at a 90-degree angle. Keep your chest up, back straight, and core engaged throughout the exercise. Push the handles downward by extending your elbows until your arms are fully extended. Keep your upper arms stationary throughout the exercise. Pause briefly at the bottom of the movement, then slowly release the handles to return to the starting position under control. Focus on using your triceps to perform the pressing motion and maintain proper form throughout. Adjust the weight on the machine as needed to challenge your muscles effectively.", sportCategory: .weightlifting, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.traditionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),


    // MARK: Fitness
    
    // Ab Wheel
    Exercise(id: "abWheel", name: "Ab Wheel", description: "Kneel on the floor with the ab wheel positioned in front of you. Grasp the handles of the ab wheel with both hands, keeping your arms straight and shoulders directly over the wheel. Engage your core and slowly roll the wheel forward, extending your body into a plank position. Keep your back straight and avoid sagging your hips. Roll out as far as you can while maintaining control and proper form, then use your core muscles to pull the wheel back to the starting position. Focus on keeping your movements smooth and controlled to maximize engagement of the abdominal muscles.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Aerobics
    Exercise(id: "aerobics", name: "Aerobics", description: "", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.other.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .timedExercise),
    
    // Back Extension
    Exercise(id: "backExtension", name: "Back Extension", description: "Lie face down on a back extension bench, positioning your hips at the edge of the pad. Secure your feet under the footpads and cross your arms over your chest or place your hands behind your head. Keep your back straight and engage your core. Lower your upper body toward the floor by bending at the hips while keeping your spine neutral. Lower until you feel a stretch in your lower back and hamstrings. Return to the starting position by extending your hips and lifting your upper body until it is in line with your lower body. Focus on using your lower back, glutes, and hamstrings to perform the movement while maintaining proper form throughout.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Back Extension (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "backExtensionMachine", name: "Back Extension (Machine)", description: "Adjust the back extension machine to fit your body size, setting the pad at hip level. Sit on the machine with your back against the pad and your feet flat on the footrest. Cross your arms over your chest or grip the handles if the machine has them. Engage your core and keep your back straight. Push against the pad with your upper back, extending your spine until your upper body is in line with your lower body. Lower yourself back down in a controlled manner to complete one repetition. Focus on using your lower back muscles to perform the extension and maintain proper alignment throughout the exercise. Adjust the machine's resistance as needed to match your strength and fitness level.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .machine, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Ball Slams
    Exercise(id: "ballSlams", name: "Ball Slams", description: "Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, holding a medicine ball with both hands. Raise the ball overhead, fully extending your arms. Engage your core and use your entire body to slam the ball down onto the ground as hard as you can. As you slam, bend your knees slightly and follow through with your arms, keeping your back straight and chest up. Catch the ball on the rebound if it bounces, or pick it up if it doesn't, and immediately lift it back overhead for the next repetition. Focus on using explosive power from your core, shoulders, and legs to maximize the intensity of the exercise.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Battle Ropes
    Exercise(id: "battleRopes", name: "Battle Ropes", description: "Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, knees slightly bent, and hold one end of a battle rope in each hand. Position your hands at hip height with a slight bend in your elbows. Engage your core and generate a wave motion by quickly alternately raising and lowering each arm. Maintain a rapid and rhythmic motion, keeping your movements controlled and your back straight. Focus on using your shoulders, arms, and core to keep the ropes moving continuously. Adjust the speed and duration of the exercise to suit your fitness level and goals, aiming for consistent intensity throughout.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .timedSets),

    // Bench Dip
    Exercise(id: "benchDip", name: "Bench Dip", description: "Sit on the edge of a bench or sturdy surface, placing your hands next to your hips with fingers facing forward. Extend your legs in front of you, keeping your heels on the ground and knees slightly bent. Slide your hips off the edge of the bench, supporting your weight with your hands. Lower your body by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your sides, until your upper arms are parallel to the floor. Push through your palms to extend your elbows and lift your body back to the starting position. Focus on using your triceps to control the movement, keeping your shoulders down and back throughout the exercise. Adjust the difficulty by positioning your feet closer or farther from the bench or by elevating your feet on another surface.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),

    // Bicycle Crunch
    Exercise(id: "bicycleCrunch", name: "Bicycle Crunch", description: "Lie on your back with your hands behind your head and your legs lifted off the ground, knees bent at a 90-degree angle. Engage your core and lift your shoulder blades off the floor. Simultaneously extend your right leg while bringing your right elbow toward your left knee, twisting your torso. Switch sides by extending your left leg and bringing your left elbow toward your right knee in a pedaling motion. Continue alternating sides in a controlled manner, focusing on using your abdominal muscles to twist and lift your torso.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Box Jump
    Exercise(id: "boxJump", name: "Box Jump", description: "Stand in front of a sturdy box or platform with your feet shoulder-width apart. Bend your knees slightly and swing your arms back to prepare for the jump. Explode upward by extending your hips, knees, and ankles while swinging your arms forward. Land softly on the box with both feet, absorbing the impact by bending your knees. Stand up fully on the box, then step down carefully one foot at a time to return to the starting position. Focus on using your leg and core muscles to generate power for the jump and maintain balance upon landing. Adjust the height of the box to match your fitness level and jumping ability.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Box Squat
    Exercise(id: "boxSquat", name: "Box Squat", description: "Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and a box or bench positioned behind you. Hold a barbell across your upper back or use your bodyweight, keeping your chest up and core engaged. Begin the squat by pushing your hips back and bending your knees, lowering yourself toward the box. Keep your back straight and knees in line with your toes. Lightly touch the box with your glutes without fully sitting down, then push through your heels to stand back up to the starting position. Focus on maintaining control throughout the movement and using your glutes and hamstrings to power the ascent.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Bulgarian Split Squat (Bodyweight)
    Exercise(id: "bulgarianSplitSquat", name: "Bulgarian Split Squat (Bodyweight)", description: "Stand a few feet in front of a bench or sturdy surface with your back to it. Extend one leg behind you and place the top of your foot on the bench. Keep your front foot firmly planted on the ground, ensuring your knee stays over your ankle as you lower into a lunge. Bend your front knee and lower your hips until your front thigh is parallel to the ground and your back knee is close to the floor. Push through your front heel to return to the starting position. Focus on maintaining balance and engaging your core throughout the exercise. Repeat on the other leg.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Burpee
    Exercise(id: "burpee", name: "Burpee", description: "Start in a standing position with your feet shoulder-width apart. Lower into a squat and place your hands on the floor in front of you. Jump your feet back into a plank position, keeping your body in a straight line and engaging your core. Perform a push-up by lowering your chest to the ground and then pushing back up to the plank position. Jump your feet forward to return to the squat position. Explode upward into a jump, reaching your hands overhead. Land softly and immediately go into the next repetition. Focus on maintaining a fluid and controlled motion throughout the exercise.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),

    // Chest Dip
    Exercise(id: "chestDip", name: "Chest Dip", description: "Start by grasping the handles of a dip station with your palms facing inward and your arms fully extended. Lift your body off the ground and lean slightly forward to target your chest muscles. Bend your elbows and lower your body by allowing your torso to descend until your upper arms are parallel to the floor. Keep your elbows flared out slightly and maintain the forward lean throughout the movement. Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. Focus on using your chest muscles to control the movement, keeping your core engaged and maintaining proper form throughout.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Chest Dip (Assisted)
    Exercise(id: "chestDipAssisted", name: "Chest Dip (Assisted)", description: "Position yourself on an assisted dip machine, standing on the platform or placing your knees on the pad, depending on the machine's design. Grasp the handles with your palms facing inward and your arms fully extended. Lean slightly forward to emphasize your chest muscles. Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the floor, maintaining the forward lean. Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. The machine's counterweight will help support your body weight, allowing you to perform the exercise with proper form. Focus on engaging your chest muscles and using the assistance to gradually build strength.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Chin Up
    Exercise(id: "chinup", name: "Chin Up", description: "Grasp a chin-up bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. Hang with your arms fully extended and your feet off the ground. Engage your core and pull your chest toward the bar by bending your elbows and contracting your biceps and upper back muscles. Continue pulling until your chin clears the bar. Lower yourself back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. Focus on maintaining a steady, controlled motion throughout the exercise, avoiding any swinging or jerking movements.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Chin Up (Assisted)
    Exercise(id: "chinupAssisted", name: "Chin Up (Assisted)", description: "Position yourself on an assisted chin-up machine, placing your knees on the pad or your feet on the platform, depending on the machine's design. Grasp the handles with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. Engage your core and pull your chest toward the bar by bending your elbows and contracting your biceps and upper back muscles. Continue pulling until your chin clears the bar. Lower yourself back to the starting position with control, fully extending your arms. The machine's counterweight will help support your body weight, allowing you to perform the exercise with proper form and gradually build strength.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),

    // Crunch
    Exercise(id: "crunch", name: "Crunch", description: "Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor, hip-width apart. Place your hands behind your head with your elbows flared out. Engage your core and lift your upper body off the ground, curling your shoulders toward your pelvis. Exhale as you lift and keep your lower back pressed against the floor. Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then lower yourself back down with control. Focus on using your abdominal muscles to perform the movement, avoiding any jerking motions or pulling on your neck.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Crunch (Machine)
    Exercise(id: "crunch", name: "Crunch", description: "Sit on a crunch machine and adjust the settings to fit your body size. Grasp the handles and position your feet under the foot pads. Engage your core and curl your upper body forward by contracting your abdominal muscles, bringing your chest toward your knees. Exhale as you perform the crunch and avoid using momentum. Pause briefly at the peak contraction, then return to the starting position with control. Focus on maintaining proper form and using your abs to control the movement, adjusting the machine's resistance as needed.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Decline Crunch
    Exercise(id: "declineCrunch", name: "Decline Crunch", description: "Lie on a decline bench with your head positioned lower than your hips. Secure your feet under the foot pads and place your hands behind your head with your elbows flared out. Engage your core and lift your upper body off the bench, curling your shoulders toward your pelvis. Exhale as you lift and keep your lower back pressed against the bench. Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then lower yourself back down with control. Focus on using your abdominal muscles to perform the movement, avoiding any jerking motions or pulling on your neck.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Dips
    Exercise(id: "dips", name: "Dips", description: "Grasp the handles of a dip station with your palms facing inward and your arms fully extended. Lift your body off the ground and keep your torso upright. Lower your body by bending your elbows until your upper arms are parallel to the floor, keeping your elbows close to your sides. Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. Focus on using your triceps to control the movement, keeping your core engaged and maintaining proper form throughout. If the exercise is too challenging, consider using an assisted dip machine or resistance bands for support.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Flat Knee Raise
    Exercise(id: "flatKneeRaise", name: "Flat Knee Raise", description: "Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides or placed under your lower back for support. Bend your knees and lift them towards your chest, engaging your core throughout the movement. Raise your knees until they are directly above your hips, then lower them back down with control, keeping your lower back pressed against the floor. Focus on using your abdominal muscles to lift and lower your knees, avoiding any swinging or momentum.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Flat Leg Raise
    Exercise(id: "flatLegRaise", name: "Flat Leg Raise", description: "Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides or placed under your lower back for support. Keeping your legs straight, lift them towards the ceiling by engaging your core muscles. Raise your legs until they form a 90-degree angle with your torso, then lower them back down slowly, maintaining control and keeping your lower back pressed against the floor. Focus on using your lower abdominal muscles to perform the lift and control the descent.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Glute Ham Raise
    Exercise(id: "gluteHamRaise", name: "Glute Ham Raise", description: "Position yourself on a glute-ham developer (GHD) with your feet secured under the foot pads and your thighs resting on the support pad. Begin with your body extended and your torso in line with your legs. Engage your hamstrings and glutes to lift your upper body by bending at the knees and hips, pulling your torso upright. Continue the movement until your body is vertical, then lower yourself back down with control. Focus on using your posterior chain muscles to perform the movement and maintain proper form throughout.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Leg Raise (Floor)
    Exercise(id: "legRaiseFloor", name: "Leg Raise (Floor)", description: "Lie flat on your back with your legs extended and your arms by your sides or placed under your lower back for support. Keeping your legs straight, lift them towards the ceiling by engaging your core muscles. Raise your legs until they form a 90-degree angle with your torso, then lower them back down slowly, maintaining control and keeping your lower back pressed against the floor. Focus on using your lower abdominal muscles to perform the lift and control the descent.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Handstand Push-Up
    Exercise(id: "handstandPushUp", name: "Handstand Push-Up", description: "Position yourself in a handstand against a wall, with your hands shoulder-width apart and your body fully extended. Engage your core and slowly lower your head towards the floor by bending your elbows, keeping your body in a straight line. Lower yourself until your head lightly touches the floor, then push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. Focus on using your shoulder and tricep muscles to control the movement, maintaining stability and balance throughout.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Hanging Knee Raise
    Exercise(id: "hangingKneeRaise", name: "Hanging Knee Raise", description: "Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your legs straight, feet off the ground. Engage your core and lift your knees towards your chest by bending at the hips and knees. Raise your knees until they are at or above hip level, then lower them back down with control. Focus on using your lower abdominal muscles to lift and lower your knees, avoiding any swinging or momentum.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Hanging Leg Raise
    Exercise(id: "hangingLegRaise", name: "Hanging Leg Raise", description: "Hang from a pull-up bar with your arms fully extended and your legs straight, feet off the ground. Engage your core and lift your legs towards the ceiling by keeping them straight and hinging at the hips. Raise your legs until they form a 90-degree angle with your torso or higher, then lower them back down slowly, maintaining control. Focus on using your lower abdominal muscles to perform the lift and control the descent, avoiding any swinging or momentum.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // High Knee Skips
    Exercise(id: "highKneeSkips", name: "High Knee Skips", description: "Stand with your feet hip-width apart and your arms relaxed by your sides. Begin skipping in place, lifting one knee toward your chest while driving the opposite arm forward in a running motion. Alternate legs with each skip, focusing on bringing your knees as high as possible. Engage your core to maintain balance and use a quick, rhythmic motion. Keep your movements light and controlled, landing softly on the balls of your feet.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Inverted Row (Bodyweight)
    Exercise(id: "invertedRowBodyweight", name: "Inverted Row (Bodyweight)", description: "Set a bar at waist height in a squat rack or use a sturdy horizontal bar. Lie underneath the bar and grasp it with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. Your body should be straight, with your heels on the ground and your arms fully extended. Engage your core and pull your chest towards the bar by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together. Pause briefly at the top of the movement, then lower yourself back down with control. Focus on keeping your body straight and using your back muscles to perform the row.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Jackknife Sit Up
    Exercise(id: "jackKnifeSitUp", name: "Jackknife Sit Up", description: "Lie flat on your back with your arms extended overhead and your legs straight. Simultaneously lift your arms and legs towards each other by engaging your core, aiming to touch your hands to your feet at the top of the movement. Keep your back straight and avoid rounding your shoulders. Lower yourself back down with control, extending your arms and legs back to the starting position. Focus on using your abdominal muscles to perform the movement and maintain a smooth, controlled motion throughout.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Jump Squat
    Exercise(id: "jumpSquat", name: "Jump Squat", description: "Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your hands clasped in front of you or at your sides. Lower into a squat by bending your knees and pushing your hips back, keeping your chest up and back straight. From the squat position, explode upward into a jump, extending your hips, knees, and ankles fully. Land softly on the balls of your feet and immediately lower back into the squat position for the next repetition. Focus on maintaining good form, using your leg muscles for the explosive jump, and controlling your landing.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Jumping Jack
    Exercise(id: "jumpingJack", name: "Jumping Jack", description: "Stand with your feet together and your arms relaxed by your sides. Jump your feet out to the sides while simultaneously raising your arms overhead, forming a star shape with your body. Quickly jump back to the starting position, bringing your feet together and lowering your arms to your sides. Maintain a steady, rhythmic pace, focusing on full range of motion and keeping your movements light and controlled. Engage your core throughout the exercise to help maintain balance and coordination.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Kettlebell Swing
    Exercise(id: "kettlebellSwing", name: "Kettlebell Swing", description: "Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and a kettlebell on the ground in front of you. Bend at your hips and knees to grasp the kettlebell with both hands, keeping your back flat. Swing the kettlebell back between your legs, then drive your hips forward explosively to swing the kettlebell up to shoulder height. Keep your arms straight and use the momentum generated by your hip thrust. Allow the kettlebell to swing back down between your legs and repeat. Focus on using your hips and glutes to generate power, maintaining a strong core throughout.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .kettlebell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Kettlebell Turkish Get Up
    Exercise(id: "kettlebellTurkishGetUp", name: "Kettlebell Turkish Get Up", description: "Lie on your back with a kettlebell in your right hand, arm extended straight up, and right knee bent with your foot flat on the floor. Use your left arm and leg to help push yourself up onto your left elbow, then extend your left arm to lift your torso. Push through your right foot to lift your hips and slide your left leg back into a kneeling position. Stand up from the kneeling position, keeping the kettlebell overhead. Reverse the steps to return to the starting position. Focus on maintaining control and keeping the kettlebell stable throughout the movement.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .kettlebell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Kipping Pull-Up
    Exercise(id: "kippingPullUp", name: "Kipping Pull-Up", description: "Hang from a pull-up bar with your hands shoulder-width apart and your arms fully extended. Initiate the movement by swinging your legs forward and then backward to generate momentum. As your body swings forward again, pull your chest toward the bar by bending your elbows and using the generated momentum. Push away from the bar at the top of the movement to begin the next swing. Focus on maintaining a smooth, controlled rhythm and engaging your core to help generate power for the pull-up.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .kettlebell, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Knee Raise (Captain's Chair)
    Exercise(id: "kneeRaiseCaptainsChair", name: "Knee Raise (Captain's Chair)", description: "Position yourself on a captain's chair or dip station, supporting your body with your forearms on the arm pads and your back against the backrest. Keep your legs hanging straight down. Engage your core and lift your knees toward your chest by bending at the hips. Raise your knees as high as possible, then lower them back down with control. Focus on using your lower abdominal muscles to lift your knees and maintain stability throughout the movement.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Knees to Elbows
    Exercise(id: "kneesToElbows", name: "Knees to Elbows", description: "Hang from a pull-up bar with your hands shoulder-width apart and your arms fully extended. Engage your core and lift your knees toward your elbows by bending at the hips and knees. Try to bring your knees as close to your elbows as possible. Lower your legs back down with control, fully extending them. Focus on using your abdominal muscles to lift your knees and maintaining a controlled, steady motion throughout the exercise. Avoid swinging your body to ensure that your abs are doing the work.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Lateral Box Jump
    Exercise(id: "lateralBoxJump", name: "Lateral Box Jump", description: "Stand to the side of a sturdy box or platform with your feet shoulder-width apart. Bend your knees slightly and swing your arms back to generate momentum. Explode laterally, jumping sideways onto the box, landing softly with both feet. Stand up fully on the box, then step or jump back down to the starting position. Focus on maintaining balance and control throughout the movement, using your legs and core to power the jump.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Mountain Climber
    Exercise(id: "mountainClimber", name: "Mountain Climber", description: "Start in a plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body in a straight line. Engage your core and drive one knee towards your chest while keeping the other leg extended. Quickly switch legs, bringing the opposite knee to your chest while extending the first leg back. Continue alternating legs rapidly, as if you are running in place. Focus on maintaining a strong plank position and engaging your core throughout the exercise.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Muscle Up
    Exercise(id: "muscleUp", name: "Muscle Up", description: "Hang from a pull-up bar with an overhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart. Initiate a powerful pull-up by engaging your back and arms to lift your chest above the bar. As your chest clears the bar, quickly transition by leaning your chest forward and pressing down with your arms to push your body up over the bar into a dip position. Extend your arms fully to complete the movement. Focus on a smooth transition and using both pulling and pushing muscles to perform the muscle-up.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Oblique Crunch
    Exercise(id: "obliqueCrunch", name: "Oblique Crunch", description: "Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Place your hands behind your head with your elbows flared out. Lift your shoulder blades off the ground and twist your torso to bring one elbow towards the opposite knee, engaging your oblique muscles. Return to the starting position and repeat on the other side. Focus on maintaining control and using your obliques to perform the movement, avoiding any jerking or pulling on your neck.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Pistol Squat
    Exercise(id: "pistolSquat", name: "Pistol Squat", description: "Stand on one leg with your other leg extended straight out in front of you. Extend your arms forward for balance. Lower yourself into a squat by bending your standing knee and pushing your hips back, keeping your extended leg off the ground. Lower as far as possible while maintaining control, then push through your heel to stand back up to the starting position. Focus on balance and using your leg muscles to control the movement.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),

    // Plank
    Exercise(id: "plank", name: "Plank", description: "Begin in a forearm plank position with your elbows directly under your shoulders and your body in a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core, glutes, and thighs to maintain a stable position. Keep your neck in a neutral position and avoid letting your hips sag or rise. Hold the position while maintaining tightness in your core and keeping your body still. Focus on breathing steadily and maintaining proper form throughout the exercise.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .timedSets),
    
    // Pull Up
    Exercise(id: "pullup", name: "Pull Up", description: "Hang from a pull-up bar with your hands shoulder-width apart and your arms fully extended. Engage your core and pull your chest towards the bar by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together. Aim to bring your chin above the bar. Lower yourself back down with control until your arms are fully extended. Focus on using your back and arm muscles to perform the movement, avoiding swinging or using momentum.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Pull Up (Assisted)
    Exercise(id: "pullupAssisted", name: "Pull Up (Assisted)", description: "Use an assisted pull-up machine or have a partner assist you. Position yourself under the bar and grasp it with your hands shoulder-width apart. Lower the resistance pad or have your partner support your legs as you hang from the bar. Engage your core and pull your chest towards the bar by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together. Lower yourself back down with control. Focus on using your back and arm muscles to perform the movement while gradually reducing assistance as you gain strength.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Pull Up (Band)
    Exercise(id: "pullupBand", name: "Pull Up (Band)", description: "Attach a resistance band to a pull-up bar and place one foot or knee in the band, depending on its length and the desired resistance. Hang from the bar with your hands shoulder-width apart and your arms fully extended. Engage your core and pull your chest towards the bar by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together. Lower yourself back down with control. The band provides assistance at the bottom of the movement, helping you to pull yourself up. Focus on using your back and arm muscles to perform the movement while adjusting the band resistance as needed.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),

    // Push Up
    Exercise(id: "pushup", name: "Push Up", description: "Start in a plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body in a straight line from head to heels. Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body. Lower yourself until your chest nearly touches the ground. Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. Focus on keeping your core engaged and maintaining a straight line from head to heels throughout the movement.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Push Up (Band)
    Exercise(id: "pushupBand", name: "Push Up (Band)", description: "Place a resistance band across your upper back and hold the ends in each hand, adjusting the tension as needed. Start in a plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your body in a straight line. Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body. Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. The band provides resistance throughout the movement, challenging your chest, shoulders, and triceps. Focus on maintaining proper form and controlling the band tension throughout the exercise.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Push Up (Knees)
    Exercise(id: "pushupKnees", name: "Push Up (Knees)", description: "Start in a plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and your knees on the ground, creating a straight line from head to knees. Lower your body towards the ground by bending your elbows, keeping them close to your body. Lower yourself until your chest nearly touches the ground. Push through your palms to extend your arms and return to the starting position. Focus on keeping your core engaged and maintaining a straight line from head to knees throughout the movement.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Reverse Plank
    Exercise(id: "reversePlank", name: "Reverese Plank", description: "Sit on the ground with your legs extended in front of you and your hands placed directly underneath your shoulders, fingers pointing towards your feet. Lift your hips off the ground by pressing into your hands and feet, creating a straight line from head to heels. Engage your core and squeeze your glutes to maintain stability. Hold this position, focusing on keeping your body in a straight line and avoiding sagging at the hips. Concentrate on breathing steadily and maintaining tension throughout your entire body.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .timedSets),
    
    // Russian Twist
    Exercise(id: "russianTwist", name: "Russian Twist", description: "Sit on the floor with your knees bent and your feet flat. Lean back slightly, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. Hold a weight or medicine ball with both hands close to your chest. Lift your feet off the ground and balance on your sit bones. Rotate your torso to the right, bringing the weight or ball towards the floor beside your right hip. Pause briefly, then rotate to the left, bringing the weight or ball beside your left hip. Continue alternating sides in a controlled manner. Focus on using your oblique muscles to twist your torso and maintain balance throughout the exercise.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Side Plank
    Exercise(id: "sidePlank", name: "Side Plank", description: "Start by lying on your side with your legs extended and stacked on top of each other. Prop yourself up on your elbow, positioning it directly under your shoulder. Lift your hips until your body forms a straight line from head to heels. Alternatively, you can place your hand flat on the ground for additional support. Engage your core and hold this position, focusing on keeping your body straight and avoiding sagging at the hips. Hold for the desired amount of time, then switch to the other side. Focus on breathing steadily and maintaining tension throughout your core.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .timedSets),
    
    // Single Leg Bridge
    Exercise(id: "singleLegBridge", name: "Single Leg Bridge", description: "Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Extend one leg straight out in front of you. Press through the heel of your remaining foot to lift your hips towards the ceiling, forming a straight line from your shoulders to your knee. Hold briefly at the top, then lower your hips back down with control. Repeat on the same side for the desired number of repetitions before switching legs. Focus on using your glutes and hamstrings to lift your hips and maintain stability throughout the exercise.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .timedSets),
    
    // Sit Up
    Exercise(id: "sitUp", name: "Sit Up", description: "Lie on your back with your knees bent and feet flat on the floor. Place your hands behind your head or crossed over your chest. Engage your core and lift your upper body off the floor, curling your torso towards your thighs. Keep your lower back in contact with the floor throughout the movement. Pause briefly at the top, then slowly lower yourself back down with control. Avoid using momentum to lift your body and focus on using your abdominal muscles to perform the movement.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Step-Up
    Exercise(id: "stepUp", name: "Step-Up", description: "Stand in front of a sturdy box or bench. Place one foot flat on the box, ensuring your entire foot is in contact with the surface. Press through your heel and step up onto the box, bringing your opposite foot up to join it. Step down with the same foot, then follow with the other foot to return to the starting position. Alternate legs with each repetition. Focus on maintaining a steady pace and using your leg muscles to step up and down, avoiding pushing off with your back foot.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Superman
    Exercise(id: "superman", name: "Superman", description: "Lie face down on the floor with your arms extended in front of you and your legs straight. Engage your core and lift your arms, chest, and legs off the ground simultaneously. Squeeze your glutes and lower back to lift your legs and chest as high as possible. Hold briefly at the top, then lower your arms and legs back down with control. Focus on using your lower back and glutes to lift your torso and legs, and maintain a smooth, controlled motion throughout.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Squat (Bodyweight)
    Exercise(id: "squatBodyWeight", name: "Squat (Bodyweight)", description: "Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and your toes slightly turned out. Engage your core, push your hips back, and bend your knees to lower your body into a squat position. Keep your chest up and back straight throughout the movement. Lower yourself until your thighs are parallel to the ground or as far as comfortable. Press through your heels to stand back up to the starting position. Focus on maintaining proper form, keeping your knees aligned with your toes, and controlling the descent and ascent phases of the squat.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Toes to Bar
    Exercise(id: "toesToBar", name: "Toes to Bar", description: "Hang from a pull-up bar with your hands slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and your arms fully extended. Engage your core and use a swinging motion to generate momentum. Lift your legs towards the bar, aiming to touch your toes to the bar. Keep your legs straight and try to control the movement with your core muscles. Lower your legs back down with control and repeat the movement. Focus on maintaining a steady rhythm and using your core strength to lift your legs towards the bar.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Torso Rotation
    Exercise(id: "torsoRotation", name: "Torso Rotation", description: "Sit on the floor with your knees bent and your feet flat on the ground. Hold a weight or medicine ball with both hands close to your chest. Lean back slightly, keeping your back straight and your core engaged. Rotate your torso to the right, bringing the weight or ball towards the floor beside your right hip. Pause briefly, then rotate to the left, bringing the weight or ball beside your left hip. Continue alternating sides in a controlled manner. Focus on using your oblique muscles to twist your torso and maintain stability throughout the exercise.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // V-Up
    Exercise(id: "vup", name: "V-Up", description: "Lie flat on your back with your arms extended above your head and your legs straight. Engage your core and lift your legs and upper body simultaneously, reaching your hands towards your toes. Try to touch your toes with your hands while keeping your legs straight and lifting your shoulder blades off the ground. Lower your legs and upper body back down with control to return to the starting position. Focus on using your abdominal muscles to perform the movement and maintaining a smooth, controlled motion throughout.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),
    
    // Wide Pull-Up
    Exercise(id: "widePullUp", name: "Wide Pull-Up", description: "Hang from a pull-up bar with your hands placed wider than shoulder-width apart and your palms facing away from you. Allow your arms to fully extend to start the movement. Engage your core and pull your chest towards the bar by bending your elbows and squeezing your shoulder blades together. Aim to bring your chest up towards your hands. Lower yourself back down with control until your arms are fully extended. Focus on using your back and arm muscles to perform the movement, maintaining a controlled pace throughout.", sportCategory: .fitness, sport: HKWorkoutActivityType.functionalStrengthTraining.rawValue, category: .bodyweight, executionType: .setsReps),

